On Oct 8, 2004, at 6:04 AM, Chris M. wrote:

> Why is the Pirates of Silicone significant (am I missing something)?

Legend has it that Apple Computer (and therefore the history of 
affordable, user-friendly personal computers) was born when Steve Jobs 
sold his bus and used the cash to produce the Apple I computer, 
designed by Steve Wozniak, in his (Jobs') garage. The bus provided the 
initial venture capital.
